Those who live an online life make sure to show themselves and so we can formulate the fundamental thesis that is hidden behind the behavior of young people.
Anyone who wants to hide something or just want to avoid the monopoly of Google can do so (starting with, for example, Scroogle using the Google search system but at the same time not voluntarily leaving traces).
There are not a few people who do not register to community pages intentionally for not being found, Google’s online applications, from text processing to image management and news collection, can be replaced with alternative versions not linked to huge server parks and that do not make up our best profile to date.
