Industry prices continue to rise
Domestic industrial sales prices in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - reports the Central Institute of Statistics of Hungary.
Industry export sales prices compared to July 2008 were higher by 1.1%, compared to the previous year, but decreased by 3.9%
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than the previous month and 3.2% higher than a year ago.
The domestic industrial sales prices compared to the previous month increased only 0.1%.
The domestic sales prices of the manufacturing sector also increased to a minimum of 0.1% compared to July.
The biggest price increases in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2,8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and shoe production with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high level of the price of plastic and chemical raw materials has caused a significant monthly increase (1,6%) in the product and chemical sector.
Prices fell in the oil processing sector (1,4%), in the production of electrical tools and machinery (0,9%) and to a minimal extent in the wood processing sector (0,1%).
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing activities remained unchanged.
In other sectors of the manufacturing industry there was an increase in prices between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sectors prices increased by 0.3% in domestic industrial sales in August, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of gas price increases carried out by the authorities since July 1.
Compared in 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the manufacturing sectors, the biggest increases were in the processing of petroleum products (32.4%).
In the manufacturing sector of metal products the price increase was 13.2%, of 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco representing a determining weight.
Prices fell in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the manufacturing of tools and electrical machinery (0.3%).
In other sectors of the manufacturing industry, the rate of price growth ranged from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total in the manufacturing industry in the past year prices rose by 10.2%.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sectors surged by 18.7% over last year’s prices.
In domestic sales among the target groups of the sectors, the highest monthly price increase occurred in August in the sectors producing investment goods (0,7%).
In the sectors that produce consumer goods prices increased by 0.3%, in the energy and after-use sector prices remained unchanged compared to the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month of last year, the biggest price increase was observed in the energy and subsequent use sectors (16.8%).
In the sectors that produce consumer goods the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a 1.4% decrease was measured.
Industrial export sales prices calculated in florins increased in August by 1.1% compared to the previous month, compared to 12 months decreased by 3.9%.
The Hungarian florin in a month weakened against the euro by 1.7%, against the dollar of 7.1%, compared with August 2007 strengthened by 7.5% against the euro and 15.9% against the dollar.
